The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, November 30, 2002 				 SA cruise to massive win
																								Centurion: South Africas batsmen gave a quality display to lay the foundation for a crushing 177-run win over Sri Lanka in the second of five one day Internationals on Friday.																								South Africa posted 317 for six in their allotted 50 overs after winning the toss and batting and then bowled Sri Lanka out for 140 in 33.2 overs to take a 2-0 lead.																								Akram in both squads																								Meanwhile, Wasim Akram was named on Friday in both the Test and one-day squads for the tour of South Africa.																								ONE-DAY SQUAD 																								Taufeeq Umar, Salim Elahi, Younis Khan, Inzamam-ul Haq (vice-captain), Yousuf Youhana, Misbah-ul Haq, Abdul Razzaq Rashid Latif, Kamran Akmal, Waqar Younis (captain), Saqlain Mushtaq, Wasim Akram, Shoaib Akhtar, Mohammed Zahid, Faisal Iqb al, Shahid Afridi, Mohammed Sami.																								TEST SQUAD																								Taufeeq Umar, Salim Elahi, Younis Khan, Inzamam-ul Haq (vice-captain), Yousuf Youhana, Abdul Razzaq, Kamran Akmal, Waqar Younis (captain), Saqlain Mushtaq, Wasim Akram, Shoaib Akhtar, Mohammed Zahid, Faisal Iqbal, Shahid Afridi, Mohammed Sami, Hasan Reza. (REUTERS) 
